  <title>Screenshot gallery</title>

  <p>Create a screenshot gallery in the following way:</p>

  <steps>
    <item>
      <p>Select <guiseq><gui style="menu">Edit</gui>
      <gui>Create Screenshot Galleryâ€¦</gui></guiseq>.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>A file chooser will open.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Type the name of your gallery.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Choose a folder into which the gallery should be saved.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>Click <gui>Save</gui> when ready.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p>The progress bar will pop up. You may cancel the process by clicking
      <gui>Cancel</gui>.</p>
    </item>
    <item>
      <p><app>Movie Player</app> creates a gallery from the random screenshots.
      The gallery will be saved in the folder you chose, as a <file>.jpg</file>
      file.</p>
    </item>
  </steps>

  <note style="advanced">
    <p>On the bottom of the file chooser you may specify the width of
    screenshots in pixels. You may also set the number of screenshots that
    the gallery will include or tick option <gui>Calculate the number of
    screenshots</gui> and <app>Movie Player</app> will set it automatically.</p>
  </note>

